## Known pricing bugs (fix before gamification)

- **Grade tier leak:** PC product correct but UI showed **raw** price ($26) instead of **PSA 9** ($59.99) for Tiffany McGwire #366 (`pricecharting_id` 1924394). `pickPriceForGrade` exists — verify grade reaches it; add tests.
- **Misleading volume:** "359 sales" = PC total catalog volume, not PSA 9 comps.
- **Fake trends:** `-60.5% 30d` computed from mixed eBay listings when PC returns null trend — don't blend ungraded comps into graded card trends.
- **Bad metadata on add:** player stored as `"TIFFANY - Mark McGwire 366"` instead of canonical `"Mark McGwire"` + set `"Topps Tiffany"`. Always run `lookupCanonicalCard` on portfolio/watchlist add.
- **`price_aggregates` dupes:** Fixed 2026-05-02 (NULL grade broke unique index). `recompute-trends` deployed; daily cron still needed.
- **Trend baseline:** `price_snapshots` table exists; needs daily cron + 7 days of data before 7d % is real.

